abstract: Users trying to access the site in English and Chinese reached the home page but were unable to complete searches.
snippet: Users trying to access the site in English and Chinese reached the home page but were unable to complete searches.
lead_paragraph: SHANGHAI — Google’s search engine was inaccessible in much of China late Tuesday. The exact cause of the disruption was not fully clear, but it led to speculation that the site was being blocked by the country’s Internet censors.

headline.main: Access to Google Is Interrupted in China
headline.print_headline: Access to Google Is Interrupted in China

byline.original: By David Barboza and Miguel Helft

abstract: Microsoft, Google and other companies are pushing to protect private information from government access.
snippet: Microsoft, Google and other companies are pushing to protect private information from government access.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — A broad coalition of technology companies, including AT&T, Google and Microsoft, and advocacy groups from across the political spectrum said Tuesday that it would push Congress to strengthen online privacy laws to protect private digital information from government access.

headline.main: Technology Coalition Seeks Stronger Privacy Laws
headline.print_headline: A Wide Call To Improve Web Privacy
